properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 3 at 1:27PM MST until January 5 at 12:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS RAMP UP ACROSS THE WIND-PRONE AREAS OF SOUTHEAST
WYOMING FRIDAY AND THROUGH THE WEEKEND...

...WINDS SPREAD EAST AND WEST AND INTO THE PANHANDLE SATURDAY...

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Northwest Nebraska Panhandle to include Box Butte
County and the southern portion of Sioux County.

* WHEN...From Saturday afternoon through Saturday evening.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel could be hazardous
for light weight and high profile vehicles, including camping
and tractor trailers. There could be an elevated blow over
risk along north to south oriented roads such as Highways 71...
385 and 26 could be especially impacted.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING
